<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Does anyone else agree that /anon is ridiculous?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Torsa">Torsa</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:52 p.m. 9/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Does anyone else agree that /anon is ridiculous?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/rallos_zek.cgi?read=186" TARGET=_self>Does anyone else agree that /anon is ridiculous?</A> (Leexa Kudrow)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> When you go into any zone, there are only

<BR>&gt; one or two people without Anonymous turned
<BR>&gt; on. I've asked about a dozen people why they
<BR>&gt; do this, and most haven't given me anything
<BR>&gt; resembling a good answer. One Dark Elf said
<BR>&gt; it was to be mysterious (which was for a RP
<BR>&gt; reason), but most said it was just to avoid
<BR>&gt; getting PKed. So, I ask you, if someone is
<BR>&gt; going to take the time to do a /who and hunt
<BR>&gt; down people near their level, don't they
<BR>&gt; have a good reason to do so? Having Anon
<BR>&gt; turned off means people can find you. Why is
<BR>&gt; that good? It's good because people can ask
<BR>&gt; you to be part of their group instead of
<BR>&gt; /shouting it all over the zone that they
<BR>&gt; need volunteers. It's good because if
<BR>&gt; someone is trying to hunt you down across
<BR>&gt; zones, their only valid reason would be a
<BR>&gt; (probably RP related) vendetta, which only
<BR>&gt; lends to the atmosphere of the game. So can
<BR>&gt; someone give me one good reason why we
<BR>&gt; should all turn on Anonymous inside Rallos
<BR>&gt; Zek?
<P>It's not they are going to hunt you down it's that they may be in a rather small zone such as MM and if they do a /who they look over and know right off your in range. With the anon on they have to guess and if someone is blue they could be 7 levels below you. Thats my reasoning at least. I admit the few times I have left it on off I have had fun with people asking me questions. I rather feel safe though.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
